AH Consulting was contracted by the Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) to support ESCOM in preparing for the implementation of the ESCOM Management Information System (EMIS), and to supervise the implementation of the EMIS by the Supplier in accordance with the specified objectives, time frame and budget. AH Consulting is undertaking project management, supervision and as well as quality assurance to MCA-Malawi/ESCOM that the Supplier has a sufficient quality assurance process in place. The assignment involved: 

Preparation 
Planning the implementation requirements of ESCOM including undertaking the strategy for the site preparation and verification process for ESCOM headquarters, regional offices and district offices;
Ensuring that the Chart of Accounts and the codification tables for transition into the new system are properly developed and signed off jointly with ESCOM before commencement of data conversion and migration; 
Supporting ESCOM with data migration and conversion process;
Ensuring that ESCOM has undertaken all the internal planned training ahead of the EMIS implementation; 
Supporting key stakeholders’ decision making through provision of documentation and communication of agreed specifications, goals, objectives, scope, outputs, resources required, budget, schedule, project structure, roles and responsibilities;
Identifying risks and implementing strategies to manage them;
Establishing priorities for critical project tasks and ensure that the responsible ESCOM team members are coordinated to execute the tasks and to ensure the successful completion of the project milestones;
Assisting ESCOM to ensure that all preparatory work required before the implementation of the EMIS has been completed.

Supervision
During the implementation phase of the EMIS project, AH Consulting undertook the following tasks:
Review of the project plan and implementation schedule developed and presented to ESCOM and MCA-Malawi by the Supplier for approval and adoption;
Technical advice and input to ESCOM to maximize the likelihood of the EMIS project achieving its planned objectives;
Escalation and resolution of issues arising in the course of implementation;
Verifying the solution design as per specifications and solution build processes for the EMIS applications;
Business continuity of operations; 
Supervising all tests required during the testing phase including unit testing, modular testing, high volume tests and integrated tests required to move into the parallel run phase;
AH Consulting reviewed and approved test plans and scripts submitted by the Supplier including:
Review the parallel run strategy developed by the Supplier and ensure that the strategy is operating as per specifications during the parallel run period before cutover.
Support the commissioning of all planned sites and the go live activities for cut over from the manual systems to the computerised systems.
Ensure that the EMIS project utilizes ‘best practice’ in large-scale project management, including quality management principles for the implementation of complex information system projects.

Project Management 
AH Consulting is assisting ESCOM/ MCA-Malawi in all contractual matters as well as Supplier management matters, such as:
Reviewing time schedules and work plans of ESCOM’s activities to ensure they are aligned with those of the Supplier;
Assessing claims by the Supplier regarding time extension and/or additional cost and providing advice to MCA-Malawi regarding appropriate responses;
Consideration and advice to MCA-Malawi regarding the approval of any variation orders. 
Coordination of all Supplier and ESCOM interfacing;
Elaborating, implementing and maintaining proper project procedures, governance and controls;
Constantly supervising fulfilment of the contractual obligations of the Supplier and informing MCA-Malawi in case of deviations;
Supporting MCA-Malawi and ESCOM in all technical, contractual and administrative matters related to the project;
Convening regular progress meetings between MCA-Malawi, ESCOM and the Supplier;
Monitoring of the installation and commissioning, reviewing and following-up on defects; 
Reporting as required under the Contract;
Checking completeness of the final technical project documentation including manuals.
